criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All the patients signed the informed consent before treatment;

          -  Who's ages are between 18 and 65 years old,American society of
             Anesthesiologists(ASA)grade are between I and III;

          -  require gastrointestinal surgery on general anesthesia.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  American society of Anesthesiologists(ASA)grade is more than IV;

          -  require emergency surgery in 12 hours;

          -  suffer from nerve disease or nerve disease or cognitive disorders

          -  has ocal skin injury(like local skin infection or anabiosis)

          -  have undergone TEAS before surgery;

          -  who have developed to intestinal obstruction before surgery.
